A4.text: Persuasion is the last novel completed by the English author Jane Austen.

A5.text: It was published on 20 December 1817, along with Northanger Abbey, six months after her death, although the title page is dated 1818.

A6.text: In the months after Austen's death in July 1817, Cassandra, Henry Austen and Murray arranged for the publication of Persuasion and Northanger Abbey as a set.

A8.text: Anne Elliot is the protagonist of Jane Austen's sixth and last completed novel, Persuasion (1817).

A9.text: Frederick Wentworth, 3rd Earl of Strafford, was a British peer born in 1732 and died in 1799.

A10.text: He was appointed a deputy lieutenant of Cornwall on 29 January 1773.
